"Uncompressed AIPs do not have pointer files, so if the key for the space "
"is changed and the original key is deleted/unknown, Archivematica will "
"have no record of the key for decryption."
msgstr ""

#: ../../administrators.rst:530
msgid "Local Filesystem"
msgstr ""

#: ../../administrators.rst:532
msgid ""
"Local Filesystem spaces handle storage that is available locally on the "
"machine running the Storage Service. Typically this is the hard drive, "
"SSD or raid array attached to the machine, but it could also encompass "
"remote storage that has already been mounted. For remote storage that has"
" been locally mounted, we recommend using a more specific Space if one is"
" available."
msgstr ""

#: ../../administrators.rst:550
msgid "LOCKSS"
msgstr ""

#: ../../administrators.rst:552
msgid ""
"Archivematica can store AIPs in a `LOCKSS`_ network via LOCKSS-O-Matic, "
"which uses SWORD to communicate between the Storage Service and a Private"
" LOCKSS Network (PLN)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../administrators.rst:563
msgid ""
"**Service document IRI**: the URL of the LOCKSS-o-matic service document "
"IRI, e.g. ``http://lockssomatic.example.org/api/sword/2.0/sd-iri``."
msgstr ""

#: ../../administrators.rst:565
msgid ""
"**Content Provider ID**: the On-Behalf-Of value when communicating with "
"LOCKSS-o-matic."
msgstr ""

#: ../../administrators.rst:567
msgid ""
"**Externally available domain**: the base URL for this server that LOCKSS"
" will be able to access. Generally this is the URL for the home page of "
"the Storage Service."
msgstr ""

#: ../../administrators.rst:570
msgid ""
"**Keep local copy?**: check this box if you wish to store a local copy of"
" the AIPs even after they are stored in LOCKSS."
msgstr ""

#: ../../administrators.rst:575
msgid ""
"When creating a Location for a LOCKSS space (see below), the Purpose of "
"the Location must be AIP Storage."
msgstr ""

#: ../../administrators.rst:581
msgid "NFS"
msgstr ""

#: ../../administrators.rst:583
msgid ""
"NFS spaces are for NFS exports mounted on the Storage Service server and "
"the Archivematica pipeline."
msgstr ""

#: ../../administrators.rst:590 ../../administrators.rst:627
msgid ""
"**Path**: the absolute path to where the space is mounted on the "
"filesystem local to the Storage Service."
msgstr ""

#: ../../administrators.rst:594
msgid ""
"**Remote name**: the hostname or IP address of the remote computer "
"exporting the NFS mount."
msgstr ""

#: ../../administrators.rst:596
msgid "**Remote path**: the export path on the NFS server"
msgstr ""

#: ../../administrators.rst:597
msgid ""
"**Version**:  the version of the filesystem, e.g. ``nfs`` or ``nfs4``,as "
"would be passed to the mount command."
msgstr ""

#: ../../administrators.rst:599
msgid ""
"**Manually mounted**: This is a placeholder for a feature that is not yet"
" available."
msgstr ""

#: ../../administrators.rst:605
msgid "Pipeline Local Filesystem"
msgstr ""

#: ../../administrators.rst:607
msgid ""
"Pipeline Local Filesystems refer to the storage that is local to the "
"Archivematica pipeline, but remote to the Storage Service. For this Space"
" to work properly, passwordless SSH must be set up between the Storage "
"Service host and the Archivematica host."
msgstr ""

#: ../../administrators.rst:612
msgid ""
"For example, the Storage Service is hosted on storage_service_host and "
"Archivematica is running on archivematica1. The transfer sources for "
"Archivematica are stored locally on archivematica1, but the Storage "
"Service needs access to them. The Space for that transfer source would be"
" a Pipeline Local Filesystem."
msgstr ""

#: ../../administrators.rst:620
msgid ""
"Passwordless SSH must be set up between the Storage Service host and the "
"computer Archivematica is running on."
msgstr ""

#: ../../administrators.rst:631
msgid "**Remote user**: the username on the remote host."
msgstr ""

#: ../../administrators.rst:632
msgid ""
"**Remote name**: the hostname or IP address of the computer running "
"Archivematica. This should be SSH accessible from the Storage Service "
"computer."
msgstr ""

#: ../../administrators.rst:635
msgid ""
"**Assume remote host serving files with rsync daemon**: if checked, the "
"Storage Service will use rsync daemon-style commands instead of the "
"default rsync with remote shell."
msgstr ""

#: ../../administrators.rst:638
msgid "**Rsync password**: the password for the rsync daemon"
msgstr ""

#: ../../administrators.rst:643
msgid "RClone"
msgstr ""

#: ../../administrators.rst:645
msgid ""
"`rclone`_ is a command-line program to manage files in cloud storage, and"
" is available as an access protocol in Storage Service 0.20 and higher."
msgstr ""

#: ../../administrators.rst:648
msgid ""
"The RClone space allows for use of over 40 cloud providers with "
"Archivematica as Transfer Source, AIP Store, DIP Store, and Replicator "
"locations. Configuration of details such as access keys can be done with "
"a configuration file or via environment variables (the recommended "
"method). See the `rclone documentation on configuration via environment "
"variables`_."
msgstr ""

#: ../../administrators.rst:656
msgid "**Access protocol**: RClone"
msgstr ""

#: ../../administrators.rst:659
msgid ""
"**Staging path**: A location on your local disk where Archivematica can "
"place files for staging purposes, for example "
"``var/archivematica/storage_service/rclone_staging``."
msgstr ""

#: ../../administrators.rst:662
msgid ""
"**Remote name**: Remote name for the rclone configuration to use with "
"this Space. Must match value in environment variables, case-insensitive."
msgstr ""

#: ../../administrators.rst:664
msgid ""
"**Container/Bucket name**: Container or bucket name to use in configured "
"remote (optional, depending on service being used via rclone)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../administrators.rst:670
msgid "Swift"
msgstr ""

#: ../../administrators.rst:672
msgid ""
"OpenStack's Swift is available as an access protocol in Storage Service "
"0.7 and higher."
msgstr ""

#: ../../administrators.rst:682
msgid "**Auth URL**: the URL to authenticate against."
msgstr ""

#: ../../administrators.rst:683
msgid "**Auth version**: the OpenStack authentication version."
msgstr ""

#: ../../administrators.rst:684
msgid "**Username**: the Swift username that will be used for authentication."
msgstr ""

#: ../../administrators.rst:685
msgid "**Password**: the password for the above username."
msgstr ""

#: ../../administrators.rst:686
msgid ""
"**Container**: the name of the Swift container. To list available "
"containers in your Swift installation, run ``swift list`` from the "
"command line."
msgstr ""

#: ../../administrators.rst:688
msgid ""
"**Tenant**: the tenant/account name, required when connecting to an auth "
"2.0 system."
msgstr ""

#: ../../administrators.rst:690
msgid "**Region**: the region in Swift. This field is optional."
msgstr ""

#: ../../administrators.rst:694
msgid ""
"Swift cannot be used for transfers containing an object over 5GB (for "
"uncompressed packages) or that are 5GB in total (for compressed "
"packages). This applies to the Transfer Source, Backlog, AIP and DIP "
"Locations."
msgstr ""

#: ../../administrators.rst:698
msgid ""
"Any object/package over 5GB must be segmented by the application "
"interacting with Swift, a function which is not currently available for "
"the Swift space. See the `Swift documentation for large objects`_."
msgstr ""

#: ../../administrators.rst:705
msgid "S3 (Amazon)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../administrators.rst:707
msgid ""
"Amazon S3 is available as an access protocol as of Storage Service "
"version 0.12. Locations within S3 can be used as AIP Storage, DIP "
"Storage, Replicator and Transfer Source :ref:`locations <location-"
"purposes>`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../administrators.rst:715
msgid "**Path**: *Not required: see below*."
msgstr ""

#: ../../administrators.rst:716
msgid ""
"**Staging path**: the absolute path to a staging area on the same server "
"as the Storage Service."
msgstr ""

#: ../../administrators.rst:718
msgid ""
"**S3 Endpoint URL**: the URL of the S3 endpoint, e.g. "
"``https://s3.amazonaws.com``."
msgstr ""

#: ../../administrators.rst:720
msgid ""
"**Access Key ID to authenticate**: the public key generated by S3. *Not "
"required: see below*"
msgstr ""

#: ../../administrators.rst:722
msgid ""
"**Secret Access Key to authenticate with**: the secret key generated by "
"S3. *Not required: see below*"
msgstr ""

#: ../../administrators.rst:724
msgid "**Region**: the region that the S3 instance uses, e.g. ``us-east-2``."
msgstr ""

#: ../../administrators.rst:725
msgid ""
"**S3 Bucket**: the name of the designated S3 Bucket. This field is "
"optional."
msgstr ""

#: ../../administrators.rst:729
msgid ""
"Not all fields are required when configuring S3 storage. They can however"
" still be used."
msgstr ""

#: ../../administrators.rst:732
msgid ""
"When a Path is configured for S3 as well as a Relative Path for the "
"Location (see `locations`_) the Storage Service will attempt to create an"
" S3 bucket to appear as follows to the user (each newline indicates a "
"nested directory):"
