#: ../../administrators.rst:764
msgid ""
"When Access Key ID and Secret Access Key are configured, the Storage "
"Service will attempt to authenticate with those details."
msgstr ""

#: ../../administrators.rst:767
msgid ""
"When these values are not configured, the Storage Service will attempt to"
" use authentication details provided by the ``AWS_ACCESS_KEY_ID`` and "
"``AWS_SECRET_ACCESS_KEY`` environment variables."
msgstr ""

#: ../../administrators.rst:771
msgid ""
"When the bucket name is configured, that bucket will be used. Otherwise, "
"the ID of the space will be used instead. In either case the bucket will "
"be automatically created if necessary, and if the AWS user has "
"permissions to do so."
msgstr ""

#: ../../administrators.rst:778
msgid ""
"For the `Path` configured in the Storage Space and `Relative Path` "
"configured in the Location, they are best configured without a leading-"
"slash (`/`) as this may impact the ability to delete stored packages on "
"the S3 service. This is an impact of the third-party library used to make"
" S3 API calls."
msgstr ""

#: ../../administrators.rst:784
msgid ""
"If users have stored packages on paths with leading slashes and packages "
"are not being removed from S3, consider modifying the configuration to "
"remove the slash. Do so with caution and be prepared to put the leading-"
"slash back if there is any impact on storing AIPs as a result."
msgstr ""

#: ../../administrators.rst:790
msgid "Debugging S3"
msgstr ""

#: ../../administrators.rst:792
msgid ""
"There are times when the S3 storage adapter may need to be debugged. For "
"example, if a transfer isn't able to complete because it cannot reach "
"your S3 implementation."
msgstr ""

#: ../../administrators.rst:796
msgid ""
"The S3 adapter written for the Storage Service relies heavily on the "
"`Boto3`_ S3 SDK (Software Development Kit). The library is hosted on "
"GitHub and the GitHub issues for Boto3 are a good place to start when "
"trying to understand potential upstream issues."
msgstr ""

#: ../../administrators.rst:801
msgid ""
"In the Storage Service, debug logging can be increased for the Boto3 "
"adapter. There is more information about overriding the Storage Service "
"defaults in the `installation README.md`_."
msgstr ""

#: ../../administrators.rst:805
msgid ""
"In the `logging configuration`_, administrators should be able to find "
"entries for the two primary Boto3 components::"
msgstr ""

#: ../../administrators.rst:811
msgid ""
"Changing the log level for these entries from INFO to DEBUG will output "
"the entire wire-trace between the Storage Service and your S3 "
"implementation through the lens of the Boto3 SDK. The standard Boto3 "
"logging will provide high-level information, and botocore will be much "
"more detailed."
msgstr ""

#: ../../administrators.rst:816
msgid ""
"From the documentation, the `Boto3 developers`_ are careful to note as "
"follows:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../administrators.rst:820
msgid ""
"Be aware that when logging anything from 'botocore' the full wire trace "
"will appear in your logs. If your payloads contain sensitive data this "
"should not be used in production."
msgstr ""

#: ../../administrators.rst:826
msgid ""
"When updating the debug configuration, if the Boto3 entries are not "
"present then they can be added manually. If adding these manually then "
"keep in mind that the change must not compromise the integrity of the "
"JSON."
msgstr ""

#: ../../administrators.rst:834
msgid "Write-Only Replica Staging on local filesystem"
msgstr ""

#: ../../administrators.rst:836
msgid ""
"Write-Only Replica Staging spaces allow users to stage AIP replicas on a "
"local filesystem for delivery to offline storage systems such as tape "
"robots. Only Replicator locations can be created in a Write-Only Replica "
"Staging space."
msgstr ""

#: ../../administrators.rst:850
msgid ""
"Write-Only Replica Staging is a write-once space. Replicas stored in a "
"Replicator location in a Write-Only Replica Staging space cannot "
"downloaded, deleted, or fixity checked after storage."
msgstr ""

#: ../../administrators.rst:856
msgid ""
"Replicas written within a Write-Only Replica Staging space are stored "
"directly within the Replicator location's path rather than within the "
"typical UUID quad directories. This enables efficient retrieval of "
"packages stored in the space by offline storage systems."
msgstr ""

#: ../../administrators.rst:866
msgid ""
"Locations are contained within spaces and have a defined purpose in the "
"Archivematica system. Each location is associated with at least one "
"pipeline. A pipeline can have multiple instances of any location, and a "
"location can be associated with any number of pipelines, with the "
"exception of Backlog and Currently Processing locations, for which there "
"must be exactly one per pipeline."
msgstr ""

#: ../../administrators.rst:-1
msgid "ストレージサービスのロケーション画面。"
msgstr ""

#: ../../administrators.rst:878
msgid ""
"A location can have one of nine purposes: AIP Recovery, AIP Storage, "
"Currently Processing, DIP Storage, FEDORA Deposit, Storage Service "
"Internal Processing, Transfer Backlog, Transfer Source, or Replicator."
msgstr ""

#: ../../administrators.rst:884
msgid ""
"**Purpose**: the function that this location will fulfill, e.g. ``AIP "
"storage``. See :ref:`location purposes <location-purposes>` for more "
"information."
msgstr ""

#: ../../administrators.rst:887
msgid ""
"**Pipelines**: the Archivematica instance(s) that will be able to use "
"this location."
msgstr ""

#: ../../administrators.rst:889
msgid ""
"**Relative Path**: the path to this location, relative to the space that "
"contains it."
msgstr ""

#: ../../administrators.rst:891
msgid ""
"**Description**: a description of the location to be displayed to the "
"user."
msgstr ""

#: ../../administrators.rst:892
msgid ""
"**Quota**: the maximum size allowed for this space. Set to 0 or leave "
"blank for unlimited. This field is optional."
msgstr ""

#: ../../administrators.rst:894
msgid ""
"**Enabled**: if checked, this location will be accessible to pipelines "
"associated with it. If unchecked, it will not be available to any "
"pipeline."
msgstr ""

#: ../../administrators.rst:896
msgid ""
"**Set as global default location for its purpose**: if checked, this "
"location will be the default location for its purpose unless the user "
"specifically tells Archivematica otherwise during processing."
msgstr ""

#: ../../administrators.rst:902
msgid ""
"When setting up a :ref:`DSpace via SWORD2 location <dspace>` the relative"
" path needs to be the URL of the destination collection for the "
"transfers. E.g.: ``https://demo.dspace.org/10673/60/``."
msgstr ""

#: ../../administrators.rst:909
msgid "Location purposes"
msgstr ""

#: ../../administrators.rst:912
msgid "AIP Recovery"
msgstr ""

#: ../../administrators.rst:914
msgid ""
"AIP Recovery locations are where the :ref:`AIP recovery <recovery>` "
"feature looks for an AIP to recover. No more than one AIP recovery "
"location should be associated with a given pipeline. The default value is"
" ``/var/archivematica/storage_service/recover`` in a Local Filesystem. "
"This is only required if AIP recovery is used."
msgstr ""

#: ../../administrators.rst:921
msgid "AIP Storage"
msgstr ""

#: ../../administrators.rst:923
msgid ""
"AIP Storage locations are where the completed AIPs are placed for long-"
"term storage. For pipelines using the default locations, the default path"
" is ```/var/archivematica/sharedDirectory/www/AIPsStore`` in a Local "
"Filesystem. An AIP storage location is required to store and retrieve "
"AIPs."
msgstr ""

#: ../../administrators.rst:929
msgid "Currently Processing"
msgstr ""

#: ../../administrators.rst:931
msgid ""
"Archivematica uses the Currently Processing location associated with that"
" pipeline to store materials during active processing. Exactly one "
"currently processing location should be associated with a given pipeline."
" For pipelines using the default locations, the default path is "
"``/var/archivematica/sharedDirectory`` in a Local Filesystem. A currently"
" processing location is required for Archivematica to run."
msgstr ""

#: ../../administrators.rst:939
msgid "DIP Storage"
msgstr ""

#: ../../administrators.rst:941
msgid ""
"The DIP Storage location is used for storing DIPs until such a time that "
"they can be uploaded to an access system. For pipelines using the default"
" locations, the default path is "
"``/var/archivematica/sharedDirectory/www/DIPsStore`` in a Local "
"Filesystem. A DIP storage location is required to store and retrieve "
"DIPs, but it is not required to upload DIPs to access systems."
msgstr ""

#: ../../administrators.rst:948
msgid "FEDORA Deposit"
msgstr ""

#: ../../administrators.rst:950
msgid ""
"A FEDORA Deposit location is used with the Archidora plugin to ingest "
"material from Islandora. This is only available to the FEDORA Space, and "
"is only required for that space."
msgstr ""

#: ../../administrators.rst:955
msgid "Storage Service Internal Processing"
msgstr ""

#: ../../administrators.rst:957
msgid ""
"There should only be one Storage Service Internal Processing location for"
" a Storage Service installation. For pipelines using the default "
"locations, the default path is ``/var/archivematica/storage_service`` in "
"a Local Filesystem. This is required for the Storage Service to run, and "
"must be locally available to the Storage Service. It should not be "
"associated with any pipelines."
msgstr ""

#: ../../administrators.rst:965
msgid "Transfer Backlog"
msgstr ""

#: ../../administrators.rst:967
msgid ""
"Transfer Backlog locations store transfers until the user continues "
"processing them. For pipelines using the default locations, the default "
"path is "
"``/var/archivematica/sharedDirectory/www/AIPsStore/transferBacklog`` in a"
" Local Filesystem. This is required to store and retrieve transfers in "
"backlog."
msgstr ""

#: ../../administrators.rst:973
msgid "Transfer Source"
msgstr ""

#: ../../administrators.rst:975
msgid ""
"A list of Transfer source locations are displayed in the transfer source "
"dropdown on the Archivematica pipeline's :ref:`Transfer tab "
"<archivematica:transfer>`. Any folder in a transfer source can be "
"selected to become a transfer. The default value is ``/home`` in a local "
"filesystem."
msgstr ""

#: ../../administrators.rst:981
msgid "Replicator"
msgstr ""

#: ../../administrators.rst:983
msgid ""
"Replicator locations can be configured to replicate the AIPs in one or "
"more AIP storage locations. Replicators can be configured for each of the"
" following protocols supported by the Storage Service:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../administrators.rst:987
msgid "Duracloud."
msgstr ""

#: ../../administrators.rst:988
msgid "Local filesystem, including GPG encrypted and write-only replica staging."
msgstr ""

#: ../../administrators.rst:989
msgid "S3."
msgstr ""

#: ../../administrators.rst:991
msgid ""
"Replicators are associated with an AIP storage location via the storage "
"location's configuration page. As such Replicators must be configured "
"before they can be selected for use alongside an AIP store. There is "
"additional information about this under :ref:`configure location "
"<configure_location>`. If you would like your replicated AIPs to be "
"encrypted, create the location in an :ref:`encrypted space <gpg>`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../administrators.rst:1000
msgid ""
"If you want the same space to have multiple purposes, multiple locations "
"with different purposes can be created."
msgstr ""

#: ../../administrators.rst:1004
msgid "Outcomes of a Replicator"
msgstr ""

#: ../../administrators.rst:1006
msgid "**One AIP to many Replicators:**"
msgstr ""

#: ../../administrators.rst:1008
msgid ""
"An AIP will be replicated *n-* times where there are *n-* configured "
"Replicators for an AIP storage location."
msgstr ""

#: ../../administrators.rst:1011
msgid "**On reingest, replicas are replaced and given new identifiers:**"
msgstr ""

#: ../../administrators.rst:1013
msgid ""
"During reingest, previous replicas will be deleted and marked as DELETED "
"within the Storage Service Packages tab. A new replica will be created "
"and marked as UPLOADED. The new replica will be assigned a new UUID. "
"Pointer files will be updated with accurate references between the source"
" and the replica and vice versa."
msgstr ""

#: ../../administrators.rst:1019
msgid "**Reingest can be used to update or delete replicas:**"
msgstr ""

#: ../../administrators.rst:1021
msgid ""
"If a Replicator is disabled, reingest can be used to selectively remove "
"replicas from that replica location. If a new Replicator is enabled, "
"reingest can be used to replicate an existing AIP in that replica "
"location."
msgstr ""

#: ../../administrators.rst:1025
msgid "**Creating and updating replicas without reingest:**"
msgstr ""

#: ../../administrators.rst:1027
msgid ""
"Replicas can also be created and updated in bulk without the need for "
"reingest using the :ref:`create AIP replicas <creating-aip-replicas>` "
":ref:`management command <management>`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../administrators.rst:1031
msgid "**Deletion of the source AIP will delete the replicas:**"
msgstr ""

#: ../../administrators.rst:1033
msgid ""
"When the source AIP is deleted via Archivematica or the Storage Service, "
"the replicas will also be deleted. Conversely, when a replica is deleted,"
" only the replica within the given location is affected."
msgstr ""

#: ../../administrators.rst:1038
msgid "Limitations of a Replicator"
msgstr ""

#: ../../administrators.rst:1040
msgid "**Tight-coupling with AIP storage in a Pipeline:**"
msgstr ""

#: ../../administrators.rst:1042
msgid ""
"Replication is coupled with AIP storage. As such, if there is a failure "
"when storing a replica, even if the source AIP has succeeded, an "
"Archivematica pipeline will still fail during processing. This affects "
"indexing of the AIP in the Archival Storage tab within Archivematica. It "
"also leaves the replica packages in staging in the Storage Service. The "
"Storage Service user-interface will clearly mark the replica packages' "
"status as STAGING."
msgstr ""

#: ../../administrators.rst:1049
msgid "**New UUIDs during reingest:**"
msgstr ""

#: ../../administrators.rst:1051
msgid ""
"Since the AIP will be given a new UUID during reingest, external services"
" tracking the packages in the Storage Service, especially replicas, will "
"need to synchronize their own record accordingly."
msgstr ""

#: ../../administrators.rst:1058
msgid "How to configure a location"
msgstr ""

#: ../../administrators.rst:1060
msgid "To create and configure a new Location:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../administrators.rst:1062
msgid "In the Storage Service, navigate to the Spaces tab."
msgstr ""

#: ../../administrators.rst:1063
msgid ""
"Under the space that you want to add the location to, click on **Create "
"Location here**."
msgstr ""

#: ../../administrators.rst:1065
msgid ""
"Choose a purpose (e.g. AIP Storage) and pipeline, and enter a \"Relative "
